Q2. What is Precision, Recall, F1-score ?

A2. ğŸ“Œ Let's say:
You're predicting heart disease (1) vs no heart disease (0).

âœ… True Positive (TP) = Person had heart disease, model said "yes"

âŒ False Positive (FP) = Person didnâ€™t have it, but model said "yes"

âŒ False Negative (FN) = Person had disease, but model said "no"

âœ… True Negative (TN) = Person didnâ€™t have it, model said "no"

ğŸ¯ Precision (Kitna sahi bola jab "yes" bola?)
Precision = TP / (TP + FP)
It answers:
"Out of all the people the model said have heart disease, how many actually have it?"

High precision â†’ kam jhooth bole model.

ğŸ“Œ Tere model ka:

Class 1 (Heart Disease): 91% precision â†’ Bohot kam fake alert diya ğŸ”¥

ğŸ” Recall (Kitne log pakde jinko sach meh problem thi?)
Recall = TP / (TP + FN)
It answers:
"Out of all the people who actually have heart disease, how many did the model catch?"

High recall â†’ kam miss kiya.

ğŸ“Œ Tere model ka:

Class 1 recall: 89% â†’ Model ne 89% patients ko pakad liya âœ…

ğŸ§® F1-Score (Balance between Precision & Recall)
F1 = 2 Ã— (Precision Ã— Recall) / (Precision + Recall)
It is the harmonic mean of precision and recall.

Use when:

You want a balance

Or when classes are imbalanced

ğŸ“Œ Tere model ka:

F1 for class 1: 90% â€” Very well balanced ğŸ”¥

ğŸ‰ Ekdam Desi Example:
Soch:

Tu police hai, aur chor pakad raha hai

Precision = Tu jise chor bola, wo sach meh chor nikla?

Recall = Jitne asli chor the, unme se kitne tu pakad paya?

F1 = Kitna tu smart aur fair tha dono ka balance bana ke

| Metric    | Tera Model | Kya Bolta Hai?                           |
| --------- | ---------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Precision | 91%        | Chor bola toh mostly sach meh chor nikla |
| Recall    | 89%        | Chor tha toh 89% chance tu pakad lega    |
| F1-Score  | 90%        | Tu smart + fair dono ho as a model ğŸ”¥    |

